To "shout out" is to express a greeting.  A "shout out" is typically bestowed in an affectionate manner.  It is synonymous with "giving props."  Many people use it to express gratitude or to recognize an individual of particular importance.  

Example:  "I like to give a shout out to all those Moot Court seniors out there.  You know who you are, Michael Broda,  Natalie Miller,  Margaux Day,  Liz Weiss,  Megan Cameron,  Jim Lazar,  Jen Woloshyn...  Stay fresh!"